Description: SPOC developed a clinical and technological platform with the ability to diagnose muscle pain associated with chronic diseases.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Business Description SPOC has developed a clinical and technological platform that promises to greatly increase the accuracy with which muscle pain is diagnosed and drive down health care costs associated with chronic pain.  SPOC has set forth to capitalize on an opportunity to work with Dr. Norman Marcus, a leading pain management physician, on developing a medical device to facilitate his revolutionary method for pain diagnosis. Market: The primary market will be pain management physicians and will then expand to sports medicine, physical therapists, and fitness centers.  There will be a parallel expansion with general practitioners at a different saturation rate due to disparity in the need for pain diagnosis in routine checkups vs. the greater need by pain and physical therapists.  Ideally the SPOC device will be as common as the stethoscope in a physicianâ€™s hand.  Signaling a new era in pain diagnosis where the idea of chronic muscle pain will be virtually nonexistent. Utilizing November 2003 Bureau of Labor Statistics data an estimate for the potential U.S. market is $1.6 billion and an additional $2 billion globally, for a total potential market of $3.6 billion. Veterinary medicine is another potential market, but quantitative analysis is pending. Market Positioning: SPOC does not compete with current methods of pain diagnosis.  Instead, SPOC will enhance current methods of diagnosis and treatment. Thus, helping realize the full value of current diagnostic tools such as MRI, CT scan, X-ray standard physical examination. SPOC will compliment the pharmaceutical industry by helping doctors to properly correlate the prescription of pain killers to the correct source of pain.  This may help patients achieve lasting relief by pharmaceutics alone, rather than more drastic procedures such as surgery. Technology: SOC incorporates two technologies, one of clinical methodology and one for device technology, for a combined diagnostic package that allows for a revolution in the accuracy and precision of muscle pain diagnosis.  The first is a diagnostic method developed over 50 years by a series of key opinion leaders in pain management.  The contemporary expert in this field is Dr. Marcus whoâ€™s patented version of this methodology allows for the diagnosis of muscles in a dynamic, natural, state (as opposed to static).  This simple feature greatly increases the precision of the diagnosis while the unique methodology provides isolation of the pain generator, increasing accuracy.  The device was developed by SPOC and incorporates leading edge technology for trans-cutaneous-electroneural stimulation, a safe, effective and proven way of stimulating muscle.  The patented Dr. Marcus method and the SPOC device are inherently linked, a powerful innovation in the management of chronic pain. History: SPOC was conceived during the Fall of 2004.  Building on a successful collaboration with Dr. Marcus on October 22, 2004, SPOC developed functional prototypes that were delivered in February 2005.  Success of the initial prototypes spurred the current business development relationship between Stevens Institute of Technology ITI, SPOC and Dr. Marcus.
Founders: Jeckin Shah, Norman Marcus, M.D., Ryan M. Stellar

Description: Public relations, SEO, social media, and marketing communication for technology companies.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Click, call, consider, inspire, email, buy – our mission is to create communications that inspire action and these are the customer actions that we strive for with every public relations, thought leadership, content marketing and marketing communications project we undertake. The David James Agency (DJA) was founded in 2003 and currently serves clients in the cleantech, wireless networking, telecommunications, semiconductor, IT services, software and power systems industries. To ensure maximum results, DJA follows the PESO model (targeting paid, earned, shared and owned media opportunities) and specializes in press releases, blog content, contributed articles or white papers, social media, direct mail and other marketing communications and content marketing activities. To engage, email: dja@davidjamesagency.com The agency provides expertise in the following areas: Media Relations - DJA has a long heritage of successful press relations, including product/service positioning, strategic communications planning, editorial outreach, press tours, spokesperson training, press release writing and article / whitepaper writing. Blogging - Blogging provides an opportunity to publish content that can both contribute to thought leadership and help your site be found by search engines. DJA helps companies stay ahead of the constant deadlines while developing engaging posts.  Social Media - There is a place for the B2B company on Twitter, LinkedIn, Google+ and even Facebook. DJA helps clients to discover the tools that are best for them and their audiences and how to execute on the best strategy to deliver awareness. Content Marketing - Creating a targeted and impactful presence for customers requires creative content with messages the inspire action.  DJA is your one stop for video, infographics, whitepapers, contributed articles, social media contest, web copy and blogs needed for successful content marketing. Web Design - A website today is the new first impression for your company. DJA creates websites that communicate your strategic messages, look good and get found by search engines. Marketing Communications - Traditional marketing communications helps to support offline sales efforts with marketing collateral and events.  DJA has experience with brochure production, corporate / product branding, tradeshow management and sales collateral. What sets DJA apart from its competitors is more than a decade of focusing on the needs of start-ups and emerging technology firms, which allows the agency to quickly master technology concepts that might take non-technology agencies weeks or months to fully grasp. DJA has a reputation of excellence, backed by clients that have been with the agency since its inception, with those same client contacts spurring relationships with many other B2B technology businesses. DJA has a deep understanding of both public relations and marketing communications and complex technology concepts, which help the agency develop plans that best advance the business goals of its clients.

Full Description: Single vineyard wines crafted by the alchemy of ocean, fog, soil and patience. At Knez Winery, we believe that the deeper and more extensive our knowledge, the better our wine will be. We start with an Anderson Valley location that is epic in its richness—with maritime influences, complex soil, a near perfect amount of sun exposure and heritage clones like Martini, Pommard, David Bruce, Wädenswil and Wente. To this, we add the beauty of science—detailed analytics and painstaking research that help us make the most of our land’s bounty. We consider ourselves stewards of the land and our farming practices are sustainable and progressive. In our winemaking, we are hands-on in the vineyard and hands-off in the barrel room. Description: SmartFunded provides an online platform and tools that help schools to collect donations from parents, businesses, and the public.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: SmartFunded provides fundraising tools to help schools collect online donations from parents, grandparents, alumni, local businesses and other members of the community. SmartFunded is a crowdfunding platform specifically designed for public schools.  It allows schools to create, manage and promote an online campaign, and then invest the proceeds in an endowment, called a SmartFund.  It is designed to replace product fundraisers, where schools send out kids door-to-door to sell items like chocolate, cookie dough and gift wrap.  By eliminating the product from the fundraiser, donors make a tax-deductible donation directly to the school, which allows the school to retain up to 95% of the proceeds.  By comparison, the average yield from product fundraisers is 25%.
Industry Groups: Education, Financial Services, Other, Social Impact
